# Welcome to Fasola app 🫘

This app is a playground for learning expo and an attempt to create useful mobile application for people trying to get
the most out of their cook books.

## Get started

1. Install dependencies

   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

2. Start the app

   ```bash
   npx expo start
   ```

In the output, you'll find options to open the app in a

- [development build](https://docs.expo.dev/develop/development-builds/introduction/)
- [iOS simulator](https://docs.expo.dev/workflow/ios-simulator/)
- [Expo Go](https://expo.dev/go), a limited sandbox for trying out app development with Expo

You can start developing by editing the files inside the **app** directory. This project uses [file-based routing](https://docs.expo.dev/router/introduction).

## Testing on Physical Devices

This app uses custom native modules (like `expo-text-extractor` for OCR) that require a development build instead of Expo Go.

### iOS Device

1. **Build and install the development client** (first time only):

   ```bash
   npx expo run:ios --device
   ```

   This will build the app and install it on your connected iPhone.

2. **Trust the developer profile** (first time only):
   - On your iPhone: **Settings → General → VPN & Device Management**
   - Tap your developer profile and tap Trust

3. **Start the development server**:

   ```bash
   npx expo start --dev-client
   ```

# App Icon: lowercase "f" in Bodoni 72

## Context

Replace the default Expo icons with a custom "f" lettermark. Dark reddish-brown (#3D0C02) Bodoni 72 letter on warm cream (#FFF5EB) background.

## Design Spec

- **Letter**: lowercase `f`, font `Bodoni-72-Book`, color `#3D0C02`
- **Background**: solid `#FFF5EB`
- **Layout**: letter centered, sized to ~60% of icon height

## Files to Generate (ImageMagick)

All output to `assets/images/`. Existing files will be overwritten.

| File | Size | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `icon.png` | 1024x1024 | Main app icon (iOS + universal). Opaque, no transparency. |
| `splash-icon.png` | 1024x1024 | Splash screen mark. Same "f" on transparent background. |
| `favicon.png` | 48x48 | Web favicon. Scaled from icon. |
| `android-icon-foreground.png` | 512x512 | Adaptive icon foreground. "f" on transparent bg, within safe zone (center 66%). |
| `android-icon-background.png` | 512x512 | Adaptive icon background. Solid #FFF5EB. |
| `android-icon-monochrome.png` | 432x432 | Monochrome variant. White "f" on transparent bg. |

## Wiring

`app.json` already references all these paths — no config changes required.

## Commands

```bash
# 1. Main icon (1024x1024, opaque)
magick -size 1024x1024 xc:'#FFF5EB' \
  -font Bodoni-72-Book -pointsize 680 -fill '#3D0C02' \
  -gravity center -annotate +0+40 'f' \
  assets/images/icon.png

# 2. Splash icon (1024x1024, transparent bg, just the letter)
magick -size 1024x1024 xc:none \
  -font Bodoni-72-Book -pointsize 680 -fill '#3D0C02' \
  -gravity center -annotate +0+40 'f' \
  assets/images/splash-icon.png

# 3. Favicon (48x48, scaled from main icon)
magick assets/images/icon.png -resize 48x48 assets/images/favicon.png

# 4. Android foreground (512x512, transparent, letter in safe zone ~66% center)
magick -size 512x512 xc:none \
  -font Bodoni-72-Book -pointsize 320 -fill '#3D0C02' \
  -gravity center -annotate +0+20 'f' \
  assets/images/android-icon-foreground.png

# 5. Android background (512x512, solid color)
magick -size 512x512 xc:'#FFF5EB' assets/images/android-icon-background.png

# 6. Android monochrome (432x432, white letter on transparent)
magick -size 432x432 xc:none \
  -font Bodoni-72-Book -pointsize 280 -fill white \
  -gravity center -annotate +0+16 'f' \
  assets/images/android-icon-monochrome.png
```

## Verification

1. Open each generated PNG and visually confirm letter is centered and legible
2. Run `npx expo prebuild --clean` or `npx expo start` to verify icons load
3. Check iOS simulator for correct icon rendering
4. Confirm `app.json` icon paths still resolve (they should — paths unchanged)
